#: src/container/containers.md:1
msgid "Single-Container Lifecycle (`perry/container`)"
msgstr "Single-Container Lifecycle (`perry/container`)"

#: src/container/containers.md:3
msgid ""
"`perry/container` exposes the OCI primitives that operate on **one container"
" at a time**: create, start, run, stop, remove, exec, logs, inspect, plus "
"image management. For multi-service stacks, see "
"[`perry/compose`](./compose.md) — but you can mix the two modules in the "
"same program (a long-running compose stack plus one-off `run()` helpers "
"against it is a normal pattern)."
msgstr ""
"`perry/container` เปิดเผย OCI primitives ที่ทำงานกับ **container "
"ทีละหนึ่งตัว**: create, start, run, stop, remove, exec, logs, inspect "
"รวมถึงการจัดการ image สำหรับ multi-service stack ดู "
"[`perry/compose`](./compose.md) — แต่คุณสามารถผสมสอง module "
"ในโปรแกรมเดียวกันได้ (long-running compose stack บวกกับ `run()` helpers แบบ "
"one-off เป็นรูปแบบปกติ)"

#: src/container/containers.md:10
msgid ""
"Every async function returns a `Promise`. The runtime backend (docker, "
"podman, apple/container, …) is auto-detected on first use; see "
"[Overview](./overview.md#backend-auto-detection) for the probe order and "
"override knobs."
msgstr ""
"ทุก async function คืนค่า `Promise` runtime backend (docker, podman, "
"apple/container, …) จะถูกตรวจหาอัตโนมัติเมื่อใช้ครั้งแรก ดู "
"[Overview](./overview.md#backend-auto-detection) สำหรับลำดับการ probe และ "
"override knob"

#: src/container/containers.md:15
msgid "Running a container"
msgstr "การรัน container"

#: src/container/containers.md:17
msgid ""
"`run()` creates and starts a container in one shot, returning a handle:"
msgstr "`run()` สร้างและเริ่ม container ในคราวเดียว และคืน handle:"

#: src/container/containers.md:19
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"import { run, remove } from \"perry/container\";\n"
"\n"
"async function runAlpine(): Promise<void> {\n"
"    const handle = await run({\n"
"        image: \"alpine:3.19\",\n"
"        cmd: [\"echo\", \"hello from perry\"],\n"
"        rm: false,\n"
"        // Production-friendly defaults: drop every Linux capability and\n"
"        // run as a non-root user. Add `cap_add` only for the specific\n"
"        // capabilities a workload actually needs.\n"
"        user: \"nobody\",\n"
"        cap_drop: [\"ALL\"],\n"
"    });\n"
"    console.log(`container handle: ${String(handle)}`);\n"
"\n"
"    // `force: true` removes the container even if still running (the\n"
"    // FFI calls `docker rm -f` / `podman rm -f`).\n"
"    await remove(handle as unknown as string, true);\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

