#~ msgid ""
#~ "The canonical \"deploy a hono app as a native binary on a Linux VM\" pattern"
#~ " — `serve({ fetch: app.fetch, port: 3000 })` via `@hono/node-server`, or a "
#~ "hand-rolled `node:http` adapter that drives `app.fetch` — currently fails to"
#~ " link because the Web Fetch FFIs (`Headers` / `Response` constructors) "
#~ "aren't pulled in alongside perry-ext-http-server. Tracked at [issue "
#~ "#589](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/589)."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "รูปแบบมาตรฐาน \"deploy แอป hono เป็น native binary บน Linux VM\" — `serve({ "
